14507904.description: This section is a mix of stone dust path (on the towpath of the 19th century Champlain Canal) and the iconic Dix Bridge over the Hudson River. From there the route is on local roads passing by woods, farmlands, river views and the active Champlain Canal.

14507915.name: EST - H - CV05h Fort Miller to Fort Edward - hiking
14507915.description: This section is along road shoulders and passes woods, farmlands, scenic views of the Hudson River, and the Champlain Canal. The northern two miles are on local streets through the village of Fort Edward.

14507964.name: EST - H - CV06h Fort Edward to Fort Ann - hiking
14507964.description: This section follows the off-road stone-dust Champlain Canalway Trail and skips between the historic and modern Champlain Canals, passing by canal locks, woods, wetlands, farmlands, and scenic vistas.

14525705.name: EST - H - CV07h Fort Ann to Comstock - hiking
14525705.description: This section has varied conditions, traveling mostly on the shoulders of local roads. A three-quarter-mile paved trail connects South and North Quarry Roads slightly south of Comstock – this is an excellent place for a quiet, scenic walk in deep woods.

14525722.name: EST - H - CV08h Comstock to Whitehall - hiking
14525722.description: This section has varied conditions, traveling mostly on the shoulders of local roads. A three-quarter-mile paved trail connects South and North Quarry Roads slightly south of Comstock – this is an excellent place for a quiet, scenic walk in deep woods.

14525764.name: EST - H - CV09h Whitehall to Ticonderoga - hiking
14525764.description: The section has sweeping views of the Adirondack Mountains, farmlands and rural Washington County.

14525835.name: EST - H - CV10h Ticonderoga to Westport - hiking
14525835.description: This section follows State Route 9N, providing sweeping views of the Adirondack Mountains, Lake Champlain and rural Essex County.

14526497.name: EST - H - CV11h Westport to Keeseville - hiking
14526497.description: This section follows State Route 22, providing sweeping views of the Adirondack Mountains, Lake Champlain and rural Essex County.

14526552.name: EST - H - CV12h Keeseville to Plattsburgh - hiking
14526552.description: This section follows State Route 9, providing sweeping views of the Adirondack Mountains, Lake Champlain and rural Clinton County.

14526595.name: EST - H - CV13h Plattsburgh to Canada Border - hiking
14526595.description: This section follows State Route 9, providing sweeping views of the Adirondack Mountains, Lake Champlain and rural Clinton County.

14526785.name: EST - H - HV20h East Greenbush to Albany - hiking
14526785.description: This section has spectacular views of the Hudson River. Of the 11 miles, 9 are off-road paths and 2 are road shoulders next to vehicle traffic. Some 7 miles follows the Mohawk Hudson Bike Hike Trail (MHBHT).

14526865.name: EST - H - HV19h Nassau to East Greenbush - hiking
14526865.description: This section is part of the Albany-Hudson Electric Trail. Heading northwest past woods, streams, lakes, wetlands and residential areas.

14526948.name: EST - H - HV18h Kinderhook to Nassau - hiking
14526948.description: This section is part of the Albany-Hudson Electric Trail. Heading north past woods, streams, lakes, wetlands, farms and small hamlets

14526985.name: EST - H - HV17h Hudson to Kinderhook - hiking
14526985.description: This section is part of the Albany-Hudson Electric Trail. Heading northeast past woods, streams, wetlands, farm lands, and small hamlets.

14530855.name: Atlantic White Cedar Trail
14530855.operator: NJ State Park Service, Wharton State Forest

14531226.name: Whispering Pines Trail
14531226.operator: NJ State Park Service, Wharton State Forest

14531370.name: EST - H - HV16h Olana to Hudson - hiking
14531370.description: The route heads north for 3 miles, on the shoulder of a state roadway and then passes through Hudson on city streets, providing access to a variety of local services.

14531387.name: EST - H - HV15h Tivoli to Olana - hiking
14531387.description: The section heads north on scenic rural roads into Columbia County following local roads through woods, farmlands, orchards and small hamlets

14531422.name: EST - H - HV14h East Kingston to Tivoli - hiking
14531422.description: The route travels to the Kingston Rhinecliff Bridge, turning east over the Hudson River. In Dutchess County the route is on the shoulders of public roads and stone-dust trail to the Village of Tivoli

14531451.name: EST - H - HV13h South Kingston to East Kingston - hiking
14531451.description: This 6.5-mile section through the City of Kingston has varied conditions.

14531487.name: EST - H - HV12h New Platz to South Kingston - hiking
14531487.description: The route follows the Wallkill Valley Rail Trail (with a stone-dust surface). The trail winds through mature woods, past historic iron works and over the historic Rosendale railroad trestle.

14531522.name: EST - H - HV11h Poughkeepsie to New Platz - hiking
14531522.description: This route begins a walk on an historic railroad bridge high above the Hudson River. The route continues runs west on the Hudson Valley Rail Trail. The final 2 miles into downtown New Paltz, is an on-road section.

14532740.name: EST - H - HV10h Hopewell Junction to Poughkeepsie - hiking
14532740.description: An off-road paved trail following the William R Steinhaus Dutchess Rail Trail passing through wooded areas, local parks, and residential communities. It ends at Walkway Over the Hudson, a spectacular historic railroad bridge high above the Hudson River.

14532851.name: EST - H - HV09h Pawling to Hopewell Junction - hiking
14532851.description: Follows the Maybrook Trailway north and west from there, passing by dense woods, farm fields, ponds and wetlands. This 15-mile section features long stretches of trail, with relatively few access points or crossroads.

14533203.name: EST - H - HV08h Brewster to Pawling - hiking
14533203.description: Follows the Maybrook Trailway north passing by dense woods, farm fields, ponds and wetlands and ends at the intersection of Route 292 and Holmes Rd. Features long stretches of trail with relatively few access points or crossroads with no public services.

14533253.name: EST - H - HV07h Brewster - hiking
14533253.description: This 1-mile Empire State Trail section is an on-road connection through the Village of Brewster, that serves as a connection between off-road trail sections running north and south of the Village.

14533331.name: EST - H - HV06h Mahopac to Brewster - hiking
14533331.description: This route begins in Mahopac and follows the Putnam Trailway north winding through wooded areas, past scenic lakes, and through small communities. There are no services on the trail: local businesses can be accessed short distances off the route.

14533382.name: EST - H - HV05h New Castle to Mahopac - hiking
14533382.description: This route runs north along the Westchester North County Trail and passes through Yorktown Heights and follows the Putnam Trailway. There are no services directly on the trail: local businesses can be accessed short distances off the route.

14533510.name: EST - H - HV04h Elmsford to New Castle - hiking
14533510.description: This section runs north from Elmsford along the Westchester North County Trail: it is quiet and parklike, buffered from adjacent development by dense woods. No services on the trail: local businesses can be accessed through short detours off the route.

14533626.name: EST - H - HV03h The Bronx (Van Cortlandt Park) to Elmsford - hiking
14533626.description: From where Broadway meets West 242nd Street the trail runs northeast, follows the former Putnam rail line into Westchester, then the South County Trail. The rail-trail is park-like and buffered from adjacent development and major roads by dense woods.

14533869.name: EST - H - HV02h Inwood to The Bronx (Van Cortlandt Park) - hiking
14533869.description: This section is an on-road connection from northwest Manhattan to the Bronx. The route follows a designated NYC bicycle route, from Dyckman Street in northwest Manhattan to Van Cortlandt Park.

14543271.via: East Greenbush;East Schodack;Nassau;North Chatham;Niverville;Valatie;Kinderhook;Stuyvesant Falls;Rossman Crossing;Stockport Centre;Empire;Stottville
14543271.name: Albany-Hudson Electric Trail - hiking
14543271.note: Part of the Empire State Trail since December 2020
14543271.description: From Rensselaer to Hudson: connects 8 towns, 3 villages, and 2 cities in Rensselaer and Columbia Counties: 85% of the route is off-road trail, built on a former (1899-1929) electric trolley rail corridor. Part of the Empire State Trails network

14543310.name: Dutchess County Rail Trail - hiking - EST
14543310.note: Part of the Empire State Trail. Mile markers start at Hopewell Depot
14543310.description: A continuous paved trail from Walkway Over the Hudson along the former Maybrook Rail corridor through the towns of Poughkeepsie, LaGrange, Wappinger to the restored Hopewell Depot at its East Fishkill Trailhead in the hamlet of Hopewell.

14543384.name: Maybrook Trailway - hiking - Putnam Trailway to Hopewell Junction
14543384.note: Most is part of the Empire State Trail.
14543384.description: A paved multi-use trail across Putnam and Dutchess counties in New York State and into Fairfield County, Connecticut. The trail travels west from Brewster through Southeast, Patterson, Pawling, Beekman and East Fishkill to the hamlet of Hopewell Junction

14543563.name: Wallkill Valley Rail Trail - hiking
14543563.note: The trail from New Platz to Kingston forms part of the Hudson Valley section of Empire State Trails.

14546752.name: Walkway over the Hudson - hiking
14546752.note: Part of the Empire State Trail network

14584830.name: Access - Bluebird Trail - Scout Trail- Hoot Owl Trail

14595339.name: Trapper's Trail
14595339.operator: Idaho Department of Parks and Recreation

14604122.name: Boarding House Trail
14604122.description: This hiking trail leaves the parking lot at the Scull Shoals Historic Area, on the east. The trail leads hikers through flat piney woods to the remains of a historic boarding house.

14607390.name: Hitchiti Trail
14607390.description: This trail is in the Hitchiti Experimental Forest and fol- lows Falling Creek and the Ocmulgee River. One section, marked 184 on the ground, is a shorter loop that does not go to the river.

14612228.name: Chickamauga Creek Trail
14612228.description: This loop trail begins and ends at the end of Ponder Creek Road. The trail crosses several stream fords and parallels a portion of scenic Chickamauga Creek. Caution: A por- tion of the trail crosses a road (Forest Service Road 250).

14619253.name: Johns Mountain Trail
14619253.description: This loop trail begins and ends at the Johns Mountain Over-look, located at the end of Forest Service Road 208. The trail follows a portion of the ridge top and connects with the Keown Falls Trail above the falls. Caution: The area above the falls is stee
14619253.source_ref:name: FS Trail 66

14619256.name: Keown Falls Trail
14619256.description: From Keown Falls Recreation Area this loop trail follows a small stream to an observation deck overlooking Keown Falls. After the trail turns away from the stream, it winds up a series of switchbacks. Caution: The area above the falls is steep with rock b
14619256.source_ref:name: FS Trail 20

14619302.name: Pocket Trail
14619302.description: This loop trail is located in the Pocket Recreation Area. It begins in the picnic area and ends in the campground. This trail passes areas with seeps and springs. “The Pocket” is a horseshoe shaped valley between Horn and Mill Moun-tains.
14619302.source_ref:name: FS Trail 69

14619333.name: Arkaquah Trail
14619333.description: Trail descends along a ridge from Brasstown Bald parking lot to Track Rock Gap. There are ups and downs, some steep along the way. The final mile has several switchbacks.  Open ridge tops provide excellent views. This trail is within the Brasstown Wildern
14619333.source_ref:name: FS Trail 29

14627903.name: Hiking Route Nike Base - Orange Trail

14627981.name: Nike Base Trails - Red Connector Trail

14653911.name: Boardwalk Trail at Lady Bird Lake

14674541.name: Monument Trail
14674541.symbol: rectangular blazes, upper half red and lower half green

14700709.name: Saratoga to the Skyline
14700709.fixme: The rest of this route, from Walden Pond up to Skyline Blvd needs to be added

14709922.name: M Mountain Run
14709922.description: The path taken by hikers during New Mexico Tech's annual M Mountain Run. Only accessible during 49ers.

14719371.name: Spring Creek Gap Conservation Area Trail
14719371.description: Broad trail through Oak and Hickory forest with a few open glades

14738780.name: Cliff Walk
14738780.description: The walk runs 3.5 miles and about two-thirds of the walk is in easy walking condition.

14870713.operator: Maryland Department of Natural Resources, Maryland Forest Service

14870804.operator: Maryland Department of Natural Resources, Maryland Forest Service

14870805.name: Monroe Run Hiking Trail
14870805.operator: Maryland Department of Natural Resources, Maryland Forest Service

14900950.name: Garden Loop Trail
14900950.description: This 1.1 mile paved trail passes the Legacy Garden.  The overlook features a beautiful overlook, gazebo and lists of the memorial trees planted in the fields below.

14900994.name: Wetland Loop Trail
14900994.description: The trail passes through a variety of habitats, including forest, wetland and prairie. Be sure to check out the prairies in mid to late summer when they are ablaze with color!

14954591.name: Sleeping Beauty Trail #37
14954591.description: The trail zigzags up through forest and over bare rock to the old fire lookout site, affording excellent views of Trout Lake valley and the surrounding peaks.

14957935.name: Filloon Trail #102
14957935.description: Filloon Trail provides access to Indian Heaven Wilderness from Little Goose Horse Camp.

14957936.name: Wapiki Lake Trail #34A
14957936.description: This trail traverses a timbered hillside to Lake Wapiki, part of Lemei Rock's old crater.

14957937.name: Lemei Trail #34
14957937.wta:name: lake-wapiki
14957937.description: This 5.3 mile trail offers views of Mounts Adams, Rainier, St. Helens, and Hood, along with views of Lemei Rock, a 5,925' promontory that juts 500' above Lake Wapiki.

14962226.name: Great Marsh Trail
14962226.operator: Town of York Parks and Recreation

14962289.name: Deep Lake Trail #33A
14962289.description: A short trail that accesses Deep Lake off of the Indian Heaven Trail #33 within Indian Heaven Wilderness.

14962290.name: Cultus Creek Trail #108
14962290.wta:name: cultus-creek
14962290.description: This popular 1.5 mile trail begins at Cultus Creek Campground/Trailhead and enters Indian Heaven Wilderness.

14962291.name: Indian Heaven Trail #33
14962291.wta:name: indian-heaven
14962291.description: From the trailhead at Cultus Creek Campground this 3.3 mile trail climbs steeply through heavy timber into Indian Heaven Wilderness.

14963028.name: Steamboat Lake Trail #70
14963028.description: This 0.5 mile trail follows the northern edge of Steamboat Lake to the Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail #2000.

14963996.name: Langfield Falls Trail #8
14963996.wta:name: langfield-falls
14963996.description: The trail parallels Mosquito Creek to a vantage point where a monument to former ranger K.C. Langfield is erected, with the beautiful Langfield Falls as a background.

14963997.name: Peeled Cedar Trail #15
14963997.description: This short trail site offers a flat, gravel surface that wanders through an old growth forest offering a plethera of huge Cedar and Douglas Firs. It also includes a standing peeled cedar tree with a interpretive sign.

14963998.name: Steamboat Viewpoint Trail #14
14963998.wta:name: steamboat-mountain
14963998.description: A short 0.5 mile pleasant trail with wildflowers in season that climbs to the top of Steamboat Mountain, a former fire lookout site, with an intertesting view of the summit of Mt. Adams.

14975546.name: Black Canyon Trail
14975546.operator: United States Department of Interior, Fish & Wildlife Service

14983753.name: North Mountain Trail
14983753.operator: Virginia Department of Game and Inland Fisheries

15013794.name: Eagle Lakes Trail
15013794.description: This short trail drops down from the Aurora Ridge Trail to access the uppermost of the Eagle Lakes.

15013795.name: Pyramid Mountain Trail
15013795.description: The trail ascends through forest to Pyramid Mountain offering views of Lake Crescent below.

15013796.name: Aurora Creek Primitive Trail
15013796.wta:name: aurora-creek
15013796.description: The Aurora Creek trail rises an astonishing 3700 feet in 3.4 miles, from the edge of Hwy 101 to its junction with the Aurora Ridge Trail.

15013797.name: Aurora Ridge Trail
15013797.wta:name: aurora-ridge
15013797.description: A steep moderate to difficult climb which follows a forested ridge past Sourdough Peak and Aurora Peak.

15020250.name: Deadfall Trail #849
15020250.description: This 1.6 mile trail starts from Deadfall trailhead off Forest Road 28.060 and ends when it meets Snow Creek Trail #890 at 1.6 miles. Generally steep, the trail traverses dense second growth forest.

15031353.name: Falls View Canyon Trail #868
15031353.description: This one mile second-growth forest canyon trail leads to Big Quilcene River among spring blooming rhododendrons, lilies, and honeysuckle.

15031354.name: Elbo Creek Trail #892.1
15031354.description: This moderate 2.5 mile forested trail ascends through to the top of a storm blow down with nice views. Some difficult sections. A great place to observe a variety of plant life in the late spring and summer.

15031355.name: Mt. Walker Trail #894
15031355.description: A 2 mile steep, forested hike through Douglas-fir, spring blooming pacific rhododendrons, salal, and Oregon Grape to the north summit of Mt. Walker.

15035594.name: Notch Pass Trail #831
15035594.description: Hiker trail only. Hike through dense conifer forest on a trail constructed in the 1930's by Civilian Conservation Corps trail crews and get glimpses of the Olympic peaks including Mt. Constance.

15036589.name: Falls View Loop Trail #848
15036589.description: The short Falls View Loop Trail is adjacent to Falls View Canyon Trail and leads to a view of the cascading waterfall into the Big Quilcene River.

15054018.name: Tunnel Creek Trail #841
15054018.description: The trail follows South Fork Tunnel Creek for past a wooden shelter. At 3 miles the trail crosses the creek and then climbs steadily to Harrison Lake and 5050 Pass. Continue for a very steep descent to Dosewallips River for a one way trip of 7.9 miles.

15059375.name: Big Quilcene Trail #833
15059375.description: This 5.3 mile trail travels along the Big Quilcene River through old growth forest and climbs to alpine meadows in Buckhorn Wilderness.

15062969.name: Little Quilcene Trail #835
15062969.description: This 4.2 mile trail starts at the Little Quilcene trailhead off Forest Road 2820. Accesses Buckorn Wilderness via a juntion with Mt Townsend Trail #839 at 2 miles.

15062970.name: Silver Lakes Trail #842
15062970.description: The trail is 2.5 miles in length and begins off Mt. Townsend Trail at 3.0 miles from the upper Mt. Townsend Trailhead.

15062971.name: Mount Townsend Trail #839
15062971.description: This trail within Buckhorn Wilderness is heavily wooded the first few miles and opens up to meadows and spectacular mountain views.

15258195.name: Murhut Falls Trail #828
15258195.description: This 0.8 mile trail goes through second growth to old growth forest around Murhut Falls. In the spring rhododendrons flower along the short trail.

15258618.name: Lena Lake Trail #810
15258618.description: The popular 3.6 mile trail to Lena Lake and Lena Lake Campground is well maintained and is a moderate grade with long switchbacks.

15258641.name: The Brothers Trail #821
15258641.description: This trail enters The Brothers Wilderness and leads through a remote canyon area called the Valley of the Silent Men.

15260064.name: Duckabush Trail #803
15260064.description: This trail follows the Duckabush River into The Brothers Wilderness and enters Olympic National Park at 6.7 miles.

15260072.name: Duckabush River Trail
15260072.description: This backcountry trail follows the Duckabush River from the park boundary to O'Neil Pass.

15260230.name: LaCrosse Pass Trail
15260230.description: Steep mountain trail climbong over LaCrosse Pass connecting the Duckabush River to the West Fork Dosewallips Trail.

15261901.name: O'Neil Pass Trail
15261901.description: Trail connectiing the Quinault River Trail to O'Neil Pass and the Duckabush River Trail.

15261902.name: Mount Hopper Way Trail
15261902.description: Primitive poorly maintained way trail that ends near Mount Hopper

15261903.name: North Fork Skokomish River Trail
15261903.description: The ttail follows the North Fork Skokomish River from Staircase to First Divide where it connects to the Home Sweet Home Trail.

15261904.name: Home Sweet Home Trail
15261904.description: Mountain trail connecting the Duckabush River Trail to First Divide and the North Fork Skokomish River Trail.

15267591.name: Six Ridge Primitive Trail
15267591.description: Primitive poorly maintained way trail that connects the North Fork Skokomish Trail to the Wynoochee Pass area.

15267592.name: Smith Lake Primitive Trail
15267592.description: Trail leads past Black and White Lakes to Smith Lake.

15267597.name: Gladys Divide Primitive Trail
15267597.description: Primiitive trail that ascends from Flapjack Lakes to Gladys Divide.

15267598.name: Flapjack Lakes Trail
15267598.description: Moderate climb through the forest to a pair of apline lakes with the rugged Sawtooth Range looming above.

15267599.name: Staircase Rapids Loop Trail
15267599.description: 2 miles with a bridge over the Skokomish River, and nice forest and river views. Starts near ranger station

15267600.name: Wagonwheel Lake Trail
15267600.description: Very steep trail to a subalpine lake.

15268369.name: Graves Creek Primitive Trail
15268369.description: This primitive and poorly maintained tral connects the Quinault River trail with the South Fork Skokomish and Six Ridge Trails.

15268370.name: South Fork Skokomish River Trail
15268370.description: This trail leads from the park boundary up and over Sundown Pass to connect with the Sundown Lake Trail.

15268371.name: South Fork Skokomish River Trail 873
15268371.description: This trail wanders through old growth forest and crosses the South Fork Skokomish River and other streamss befoe climbing up the national park boundary.

15268372.name: Wynoochee Pass Trail #874
15268372.description: This short trail starts at the Wynoochee Pass Trailhead and travels through heavy forest to the national park boundary.

15268373.name: Wynoochee Pass Trail
15268373.description: Thre trail runs form the park boundary over Wynoochee Pass and down to connect with the Graves Creek and Sundown Lake Trails.

15268374.name: Sundown Lake Trail
15268374.description: This trail connects Lake Sundown to the Wynoochee Pass, South Fork Skokomish River, and Graves Creek Trails.

15268391.name: Pine Lake Trail
15268391.description: Walk along a gentle road-to-trail conversion along beautiful old growth groves to a placid lake deep in the Lower Skokomish Valley.

15268422.name: Church Creek Trail #871
15268422.description: This fairly steep 3.5 mile trail follows Church Creek towards a pass through a conifer forest, eventually ending near Satsup Lakes on Forest Road #2372.

15269937.name: East Fork Quinault River Trail
15269937.description: a long trail leading up the valley of the Quinault River to Enchanted Valley and the alpine slopes of Anderson Pass.

15269938.name: Hart Lake Way Trail
15269938.description: Short trail leads to Hart Lake.

15269939.name: LaCrosse Basin Way Trail
15269939.description: This trail leads up into the alpine valley of LaCrosse Basin and LaCrosse Lake.

15270573.name: West Fork Dosewallips River Trail
15270573.description: The trail begins at Dose Forks and climbs up the valley of the West Fork Dosewallips River to Anderson Pass.

15270574.name: Anderson Moraine Primitive Trail
15270574.description: Short trail leading up to the Anderson Glacier Moraine for views of Mount Anderson and the remants of the Anderson Glacier.

15270631.name: Home Sweet Home Camp Trail
15270631.description: Short trail leading to the Home Sweet Home campsite.

15270942.name: Mildred Lakes Trail #822
15270942.description: The Mildred Lakes trail is a boot path made by the feet of many hikers and fishermen. It is a root-strewn climb to the lakes. In places, it becomes steep and difficult to follow.

15270961.name: Putvin Trail #813
15270961.description: This trail climbs steeply up the side of the Hamma Hamma River Valley before entering the national park and cresting at the Lake of the Angels.

15273179.name: Mt. Washington Trail
15273179.description: Verty steep trail leading to the top of Mount Washington. Hard to follow in places.

15273180.name: Jefferson Pass Trail #800
15273180.description: This short trail climbs at a gentle grade through mature fir and hemlock forest. The elevation is comparatively high, yet the firs are 3 feet or more in diameter, with an open understory.

15273181.name: Mount Ellinor Connector Trail #827.2
15273181.description: Trail connecting the Big Creek Loop Trail to the Mount Ellinor Trail.

15273182.name: Upper Big Creek Loop Trail #827.1
15273182.description: This trail loops around the Big Creek valley below Mount Ellinor.

15273183.name: Big Creek Campground Trail #827
15273183.description: Short trail looping around the campground.

15273589.name: Dosewallips River Road
15273589.description: Hike along the closed Dosewallips River Road to the former campground.

15283835.name: Hayden Pass Trail
15283835.description: This trail connects the Elwha River Trail to the Dosewallips River Trail via Hayden Pass.

15283836.name: Lost Pass Trail
15283836.description: This steep trail climbs from Dose Meadows up to Lost Pass where it connects to the Cameron Creek Trail.

15283837.name: Dosewallips River Trail
15283837.description: The trail follows the main fork of the Dosewallips River from the Dose Ranger Station to Hayden Pass.

15283980.name: Upper Gray Wolf River Trail
15283980.description: The trail climbs from the park boundary along the Gray Wolf River to Gray Wolf Pass.

15283981.name: Gray Wolf Pass Trail
15283981.description: Thiis trail climbs from the Dosewallips River Trail up to Gray Wolf Pass.

15297366.name: California Mission Trail - stage 06 Mission San Buenaventura, Ventura to Mission Santa Barbara

15297589.name: Lake Constance Route
15297589.description: Very steep and rough trail which requires the use of hands in places which takes the hiker to the alpine setting of Lake Constance.

15297590.name: Constance Pass Trail
15297590.description: This trail through many switchbacks, lifts the hiker out of the Dosewallips River Valley up to the high alpine county of Constance Pass.

15313428.name: California Mission Trail - stage 08 - Mission Santa Inés to Mission La Purisma Conception

15313429.name: California Mission Trail - stage 07 Mission Santa Barbara to Mission Santa Inés

15318299.to: Mission San Luis Obispo de Tolosa
15318299.name: California Mission Trail - stage 09 Mission La Purisima Concepcion to Mission San Luis Obispo

15322907.from: Mission San Luis Obispo de Tolosa
15322907.name: Calisfornia Mission Trail - stage 10 Mission San Luis Obispo de Tolosa to Mission San Miguel Arcangel

15330518.name: HikANation Historical Route
15330518.description: The original route of the 1980-81 HikANation cross country hike from San Francisco to Cape Henlopen Delaware

15336702.name: Kalaloch Creek Nature Trail
15336702.description: 1.0 mile easy loop through coastal forest, with stairs and elevation change less than 40 feet.

15442957.name: Monkey Mountain Nature Reserve NorthEast
15442957.description: Hiking trail through the woods and meadows, footpath not always visible in meadows and vegitation may encroach the path with some steep sections and occasional obstacles less than 8\"

15442958.name: Monkey Mountain Nature Reserve Southwest
15442958.description: Hiking trail through the woods, a continuous established footpath but vegitation may encroach the path with some steep sections and occasional obstacles less than 8\"

15520877.name: Tombstone Lake Trail #55
15520877.wta:name: thomas-lake
15520877.description: Tombstone lake trail #55 in the Indian Heaven Wilderness leaves from the Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail #2000 near the east shore of Blue Lake and ends 0.5 mile away at Tombstone Lake.

15520878.name: Thomas Lake Trail #111
15520878.wta:name: thomas-lake
15520878.description: This 3.3 mile heavily used trail passes numerous lakes prior to its connection with the Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail #2000 within Indian Heaven Wilderness.

15520879.name: East Crater Trail #48
15520879.wta:name: east-crater
15520879.description: This moderately used trail is one of the main access routes from the east into the central part of Indian Heaven Wilderness. Trail features include small lakes, ponds, marshes, meadows, wildflowers, and Junction Lake.

15522116.name: Little Huckleberry Trail #49
15522116.description: This trail climbs a long, forested ridge on the north side of Little Huckleberry Mountain.

15537172.name: Liberty Bend Trail
15537172.description: A level trail along the Missouri River and through the woods in the flood plain.

15537539.name: Shortcut Trail #171A
15537539.description: Trail #171A is a 0.5 shortcut trail that connects Race Track Trail #171 to Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail #2000 within Indian Heaven Wilderness.

15537540.name: Indian Race Track Trail #171
15537540.description: The trail travels through second growth forest, rocky terrain , a meadow and ends near Red Mountain fire lookout. The meadow was the site of annual gatherings of Native Americans during huckleberry season.

15551230.name: Wood Lake Trail #185
15551230.description: This trail lies in the northern section of Indian Heaven Wilderness. The trail begins on the Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail north of the junction with Cultus Creek Trail #108. It descends through semi-open areas to the edge of Wood Lake.

15551235.name: Chenamus Lake Trail #29A
15551235.description: Located in the north portion of the Indian Heaven Wilderness, Chenamus Trail #29A begins at the northeast end of Placid Lake via Placid Lake Trail #29. It proceeds part way around the lake then climbs south to Chenamus Lake.

15551236.name: Placid Lake Trail #29
15551236.description: This heavily used trail begins on the northwest side of Indian Heaven Wilderness. Placid Lake, meadows, wildflowers, and a small lake are features along this trail.

15554207.name: Hand Shake Trail #67
15554207.description: This is a short, accessible trail that leads to monument honoring the Hand Shake agreement of 1932.

15554208.name: Sawtooth Mountain Trail #107
15554208.description: This trail is a former section of the Pacific Crest Trail which was relocated to skirt the lower west flank Sawtooth Mountain. The trail climbs to near the top of the mountain providing wonderful views of Mt. Adams, Mt. Rainier and Mt. St. Helens.

15554214.name: Elk Lake Trail #176
15554214.description: Located in the mid-section of Indian Heaven Wilderness, this short trail takes off from the Pacific Crest Trail near Bear Lake and drops down to Elk Lake (4,685' elevation). This trail offers fishing opportunities in Elk Lake and Bear Lake.

15554215.name: Lemei Lake Trail #179
15554215.description: Beginning at Indian Heaven Trail #33 near Clear Lake, the trail travels south past Lemei Lake. It ends at the Pacific Crest Trail near Junction Lake (4,730' elevation).

15554315.name: Valley Ski Trail #151
15554315.description: The trail passes through the forest, descends into the Wind River Valley, and crosses a bridge over the Wind River. After the bridge it climbs up to a clearcut and intersects with Forest Road 3053.

15554316.name: Terminator Trail #159
15554316.description: This 4.2 mile trail is mainly a winter cross-country ski trail, and makes a loop when combined with McClellan Trail #157.

15554317.name: McClellan Meadows Trail #157
15554317.description: The trail follows the route of George McClellan's 1852 railroad survey. A popular but challenging mountain biking trail with a grades and stream crossings.

15556917.name: Falls Creek Trail #152
15556917.description: The gradual grade of this 9 mile trail slowly climbs away from Falls Creek and crosses 2 creeks before reaching the waterfall in approximately 2.5 miles.

15556918.name: Falls Creek Falls Trail #152A
15556918.description: This trail provides spectacular views of the white water of Falls Creek. The mist from the cascades of Falls Creek creates an excellent area to rest among a blanket of mosses.

15569793.name: Big Fill Loop Path
15569793.description: The trail showcases the Central Pacific's Big Fill and the abutments that once supported the Union Pacific's Big Trestle

15590822.name: Big Slide Primitive Trail 195
15590822.description: This trail connects Trails #192.2 Trapper Creek and #132 Observation, forming a loop opportunity in Trapper Creek Wilderness. The trail has a very steep grade, poor tread, and is difficult to follow. Recommended for experienced hikers only.

15590823.name: Soda Peaks Lake Trail #133
15590823.description: This 5.5 mile trail accesses the southwest corner of Trapper Creek Wilderness. Soda Peaks Lake, a glacial -carved cirque, is surrounded by conifers in a mountainous setting.

15590824.name: Rim Primitive Trail #202
15590824.description: This trail connects Primitive Trail #198 and Trapper Creek Trail #192.2 within Trapper Creek Wilderness andl is recommended for experienced hikers only.

15590825.name: Sunshine Primitive Trail #198
15590825.description: This trail links Trails #192.2 Trapper Creek and #132 Observation to form a loop opportunity within Trapper Creek Wilderness.

15590826.name: Observation Peak Trail #132A
15590826.description: This 0.5 of a mile trail located in Trapper Creek Wilderness off Observation Trail #132 and leads to the summit of Observation Peak the site of an old fire lookout.

15590827.name: Observation Trail #132
15590827.description: This trail provides access to Trapper Creek Wilderness. Beautiful wildflowers and Bear Grass are abundant along the trail in season. The trail provides majestic views of Mt. Adams, Mt. Rainier, and Mount St. Helens.

15590828.name: Big Hollow Trail #158
15590828.description: The 3.2 mile Big Hollow Trail begins on Forest Road 64 at Big Hollow Trailhead and climbs steadily to its terminus on Observation Trail #132 at the Trapper Creek Wilderness boundary.

15590829.name: Dry Creek Trail #194
15590829.description: This 4 mile trail runs north and south to the east of Trapper Creek Wilderness. This trail offers the opportunity to hike through an old-growth forest. Views of sparkling Dry Creek and the turbulent Bourbon Creek enhance this trail.

15590830.name: Trapper Creek Trail #192
15590830.description: The trail follows Trapper Creek through the Trapper Creek Wilderness climbing steeply up to a junction with the Big Hollow Trail near Sister Rocks.

15590864.name: Shortcut Trail #132B
15590864.description: This is a primitive short cut trail between Trapper Creek Trail #192 and Observation Trail #132 within Indian Heaven Wilderness.

15590865.name: Deer Way #209
15590865.description: The trail forms a loop, running parallel with Trapper Creek Trail #192.2 for just short of a mile. The trail crosses a branch of Trapper Creek, then ends on Trail #192. This trail is recommended for experienced hikers only.

15595815.name: Coleman Weedpatch Trail #121
15595815.description: Trail #121 starts on Forest Road 2160 a few miles before Walupt Lake Campground at the Coleman Weedpatch Trailhead. The trail heads south along the border of Goat Rocks Wilderness through dense second growth conifers and ends on the Pacific Crest Trail.

15595816.name: Walupt Lake Trail #101
15595816.description: Beginning in the Walupt Lake Campground, the trail follows the lakeshore until reaching Walupt Creek. At the end of the lake the trail climbs into an open alpine area before meeting the Pacific Crest Trail.

15595817.name: Nannie Ridge Trail #98
15595817.description: The trail branches off Walupt Lake Trail #101 a short distance from the campground and climbs steeply northeast onto an open, scenic ridgetop within Goat Rocks Wilderness. The trail follows the ridge, ending on the Pacific Crest Trail near Sheep Lake.

15603040.name: Jordan Creek Trail #94
15603040.description: This trail provides access to Goat Ridge above Jordan Basin within Goat Rocks Wilderness.

15603041.name: Lily Basin Trail #86
15603041.description: This trail provides access to the Goat Rocks Wilderness. Views of Packwood Lake and Mt. Rainier are available from this trail. Parts of this trail may have been a Native American travel route, used by mountain goat hunters.

15603042.name: Bypass Trail #97
15603042.description: Connects the Snowgrass Trail with the Pacific Crest Trail to the south. This trail was also part of the original Klickitat Trail.

15603043.name: Goat Ridge Lookout Trail #95A
15603043.description: The trail climbs Goat Ridge to the former site of a fire lookout, then descends north to connect with Trail #95 again. This 1.1 mile loop offers excellent views.

15603044.name: Goat Ridge Trail #95
15603044.description: The trail climbs steeply up Goat Ridge to a junction with the Lily Basin Trail.

15603045.name: Snowgrass Trail #96
15603045.description: The trail is a major entry point to the Goat Rocks Wilderness following the Goat Creek drainage and climbing up to a junction with the Pacific Crest Trail.

15610067.name: Klickitat Trail #7
15610067.description: The 17.1 mile Klickitat Trail is a major ridgetop trail, extending from Kilborn Creek to Elk Peak. Features include ridgetop views, Castle Butte, Jackpot Lake, St. Michaels Lake, and St. John Lake.

15620227.name: Green Mountain Viewpoint Trail #110A
15620227.description: This is a short trail that climbs to the summit of Green Mountain.

15620228.name: Green Mountain Trail #110
15620228.description: This trail offers views of Mount St. Helens, Mt. Adams, and Mt. Rainier. Wild flower viewing and huckleberry picking occur along the trail as well.

15620229.name: Spring Creek Trail #115
15620229.description: Spring Creek Trail is believed to have been a Native American travel route between berry picking camps at Horseshoe Lake and fishing sites along the Cispus River. Several peeled cedar trees can be seen near the trailhead.

15627233.name: Killen Connector Trail #113A
15627233.description: Connects Horseshore Lake Campground to Killen Creek Trailhead.

15627234.name: Killen Creek Trail #113
15627234.description: Historically used for berry-picking and for sheepherding on Mt. Adams, the Killen Creek Trail climbs through forested areas and open meadows within Mt. Adams Wilderness. It offers spectacular views of Mt. Adams and meadows full of wildflowers in season.

15627235.name: Loop Trail #120A
15627235.description: Connects Keenes Trail to Horseshoe Lake.

15627236.name: High Lakes Trail #116
15627236.description: Wildflowers, huckleberries, volcanic features, high elevation lakes, and spectacular views dominate this historic trail, which was once used by Yakama Indians picking berries in the high lakes area.

15627237.name: Keenes Trail #120
15627237.description: The trail begins in the Keenes Horse Camp and provides access to Spring Creek Trail #115, High Lakes Trail #116, and Horseshoe Lake. Horses and mules share the heavily used route with hikers and bicycles as they pass through forests and meadows.

15627238.name: Muddy Meadows Trail #13
15627238.description: The Muddy Meadows trail leads into the Mount Adams Wilderness. Running through forested areas and crossing meadows it connects with the Pacific Crest Trail and ends at the High Line Trail.

15629950.name: Highline Trail #114
15629950.description: The Highline trail traveverses the north side of Mt. Adams within Mt. Adams Wilderness and rises in elevation to nearly 7,800'. The trail features spectacular views of Lyman and Lava Glaciers, as well as panoramic views of the Goat Rocks and Mt. Rainier.

15638768.name: Hamilton Ridge Trail #109A
15638768.description: This trail connects the Hamilton Buttes Trail #118 to the Hamilton Peak Tral #109.

15638769.name: Hamilton Peak Trail #109
15638769.description: The Hamilton Butte Lookout was built in 1929. The lookout was abandoned in the 1960s. Look for sections of phone line left along this trail. This historic phone line linked the lookout with the world below.

15638770.name: Hamilton Buttes Trail #118
15638770.description: On the south end, the Hamilton Buttes Trail climbs through scattered old growth and second growth forests before entering open fields on top where you get views of Mt. Adams and the Cispus River. The trail follows the ridge through several open meadows.

15649496.name: Montreal Falls Trail
15649496.fixme: Needs Ascent gain for both Main and Excursion routes, as well as trail quality.
15649496.description: A trail along the Superior shoreline. Main route goes to the Lower Falls, with extra trail leading to the Upper Falls

15652494.name: Blue Lake Butte Trail #119
15652494.description: This trail climbs steadily from Forest Road 78 for 1 mile to a semi-open ridgetop where Mt. Adams and Hamilton Buttes can be seen. The trail continues to the junction with the more heavily used Blue Lake Ridge Trail #271 near Blue Lake.

15652495.name: Mouse Lake Trail #271C
15652495.description: This short trail connects the Blue Ridge Trail #271 to Road 7812-642 passing by Mouse Lake.

15652496.name: Blue Lake Ridge Trail #271
15652496.description: This 11.7 mile multiple use trail climbs steadily through conifer forests and has heavy use. A short section of the trail above Blue Lake is \"Hiker Only\" to minimize noise near the lake.

15652497.name: Valley Trail #270
15652497.description: This trail has a gentle grade, with views of the Cispus River Valley and Tongue Mountain.

15696944.fixme: Trail route was created prior to the creation of the hiking relation on 2023/04/08. It is presumed to be accurate, but should be verified.

15949654.name: Upper La Luz, Crest House Spur, Crest Loop Route
15949654.description: This is a great summer hiking loop with city views. Ascent is about 522 ft.  Crest and Upper La Luz trails have gentle slopes of 4% in this loop.  Crest Spur has a slightly above medium slope of about 13%.  Not recommended in winter due to deep snow.

15949897.name: Tram to Kiwanis Cabin  via Kiwanis Cabin Trail
15949897.description: An easy hike starting at the Tram and going to Kiwanis Cabin via Kiwanis Cabin Trail.  Plenty of shade and wonderful city views from the Kiwanis Cabin.

15949898.name: Tram to Kiwanis Cabin vis Kiwanis Meadow Road
15949898.description: An easy hike starting at the Tram and going to Kiwanis Cabin via Kiwanis Meadow Road Trail.  Plenty of shade and wonderful city views from the Kiwanis Cabin.

15949992.description: A loop hike starting at the Crset and going to Kiwanis Cabin.
